This paper presents a novel coreset construction algorithm for solving classification tasks using Support Vector Machines (SVMs) in a computationally efficient manner. The paper focuses on machine learning and optimization techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of SVMs in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. Finally, the paper presents empirical results on real-world datasets, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
